'''Watatsumi no Miko Shrine''' (わたつみのみこじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} located in {{ill|lt=Nagasaki Prefecture|Q169376|WD=Q169376|1=Nagasaki Prefecture}}, {{ill|lt=Tsushima City|Q991032|WD=Q991032|1=Tsushima, Nagasaki}}, {{ill|lt=Toyotama Town|Q11633965|WD=Q11633965|1=Toyotama}}.

=== Overview ===
Originally, it was a Tenjin shrine and had no connection to Watatsumi no Miko Shrine. It is said to have begun on July 25 of the 5th year of {{ill|lt=Jōwa|Q1146143|WD=Q1146143|1=Jōwa (Muromachi period)}} ({{ill|lt=1349|Q6090|WD=Q6090|1=1349}}), when a Tenmangū was invited (kanjō) from {{ill|lt=Chikuzen Province|Q1047664|WD=Q1047664|1=Chikuzen Province}} {{ill|lt=Dazaifu|Q144845|WD=Q144845|1=Dazaifu (government)}}.<ref>Hirayama Tsunefusa, ‘[https://dl.ndl.go.jp/info:ndljp/pid/956888 Tsushima Kiji]’ (Tsushima Kiji Publication Society, 1917)</ref>

In the early {{ill|lt=Meiji|Q3125096|WD=Q3125096|1=Meiji era}} period, it was renamed Watatsumi no Miko Shrine. This change was due to {{ill|lt=Kaijin Shrine|Q11559099|WD=Q11559099|1=Kaijin Shrine}} adopting the name {{ill|lt=Watatsumi Shrine|Q18457651|WD=Q18457651|1=Watazumi Shrine}}.

